      },
      "text": "Urinary Tract Infections\nUncomplicated - confined within the bladder\nClinical features:\nDysuria \nUrinary frequency\nSuprapubic tenderness\nDiagnosis and management:\nUrinalysis - positive leukocyte esterase and nitrates\nEmpiric \ntreatment\n with TMP-SMX (3 days), nitrofurantoin (5 days) or fosfomycin (single dose)\nFluoroquinolones if high local resistance rates or sulfa allergy\nComplicated - extends beyond the bladder\nClinical features:\nFever\nChills or rigors\nFlank pain or costovertebral angle tenderness\nDiagnosis and management:\nUrine \nculture\n prior to empiric therapy to tailor antibiotics \nUsually oral fluoroquinolones are enough, but IV ceftriaxone while awaiting culture may be necessary in severe cases",
      "textBlocks": [
        {
          "textBlockId": "Internal_Medicine_Shelf_Fast_Facts_s0004_b9d7bc22_text01",
          "text": "Urinary Tract Infections",
          "bounds": {
            "x": 311700,
            "y": 445025,
            "cx": 8520600,
            "cy": 572700
          }
        },
        {
          "textBlockId": "Internal_Medicine_Shelf_Fast_Facts_s0004_b9d7bc22_text02",
          "text": "Uncomplicated - confined within the bladder\nClinical features:\nDysuria \nUrinary frequency\nSuprapubic tenderness\nDiagnosis and management:\nUrinalysis - positive leukocyte esterase and nitrates\nEmpiric \ntreatment\n with TMP-SMX (3 days), nitrofurantoin (5 days) or fosfomycin (single dose)\nFluoroquinolones if high local resistance rates or sulfa allergy",
          "bounds": {
            "x": 311700,
            "y": 1152475,
            "cx": 3999900,
            "cy": 3416400
          }
        },
        {
          "textBlockId": "Internal_Medicine_Shelf_Fast_Facts_s0004_b9d7bc22_text03",
          "text": "Complicated - extends beyond the bladder\nClinical features:\nFever\nChills or rigors\nFlank pain or costovertebral angle tenderness\nDiagnosis and management:\nUrine \nculture\n prior to empiric therapy to tailor antibiotics \nUsually oral fluoroquinolones are enough, but IV ceftriaxone while awaiting culture may be necessary in severe cases",
          "bounds": {
            "x": 4832400,
